We are switching to swerve drive for the first time with full kraken motors. While we were testing today, after changing the battery one of our motors stopped working completely. We never used the motor before so it was brand new. We didn’t use it either, we were just giving power and giving IDs from Phoenix Tuner. We had given it an ID yesterday evening, so we know the motor wasn’t faulty. I’ve checked the power cables and they do give 12V outputs. Although the cables transmit the power, the kraken won’t power on, the leds don’t work and I can’t see it on Phoenix Tuner either. We also installed the latest software update before it stopped working so it’s not likely that it is an issue related to software. Can anyone help?

Hey, we found a solution! We were having the same problem until we found out that the galvanized screws that hold the power board to the Kraken itself were what conducts the electricity to power the Kraken. Turns out, we only put two of the screws in LOL

20250208_1136261740×1816 190 KB

Make sure you have these screws in, as well as the other two up top.
